2. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - Grasp planning often involves analyzing visual data to identify objects and their properties, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses various grasp planning algorithms, which may involve machine learning or other AI techniques. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - As mentioned above, machine learning may be used in grasp planning, making this sub-category a possibility. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - Multi-fingered robot grasping involves controlling the movement and force of robotic fingers, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
